  <!-- SECTION: SANCTUARY -->
  <section class="section sanctuary-section" id="sanctuary">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sanctuary-inner">
        <span class="section-tag">06 / Beyond the Music</span>
        <blockquote class="sanctuary-quote">
          <p>Circuit music is only one dimension of the circuit party. Beneath the sound, the spectacle, and the physical release lies something deeper: sanctuary. In a world that has too often met queer life with shame, punishment, or erasure, the circuit party can become more than celebration. It can become a temporary refuge, a space of collective euphoria, recognition, and release, where bodies are not hidden, love is not explained, and belonging does not need permission. For a moment, people step into a world shaped by one another. Then they return to one that has not always offered the same grace, carrying with them the memory of what it felt like to be fully present, unguarded, and, if only for a night, at home.</p>
          <footer class="sanctuary-attribution">&mdash; Curtis Baldwinson</footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

